<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Mutuals are a feature that allows the user to view mutual friends or groups of other users. This feature is rolling out slowly over time.<ref>[https://docs.vrchat.com/docs/vrchat-202542#mutuals VRChat 2025.4.2]</ref>
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
There are two ways to see mutuals, in the Quick Menu or the Main Menu with a button "Show X Mutuals". In the Quick Menu, the button can be found on top of user actions. In the Main Menu, the button will be found on the top right, next to the report button.  If you wish to prevent other users from seeing your mutual friends and groups or appearing as so for others, you can turn off "Show Mutual Connections" in the '''Comfort & Safety''' section of your settings in the Main Menu. Doing so will change the text of the button from "Show X Mutuals" to "No Known Mutuals". Additionally, your user icon will be hidden and your username will appear as "Hidden Mutual" when you appear in the mutuals in one of your friends.
</div>

